  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version: latest\r\n\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nThe byte code template for the forwarder in `create_with_code_of()` is both longer than it needs to be and doesn't support returning data with the return data location from the proxied contracts.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nAn example of a template that I have built some time ago and has support for the return data location is:\r\nhttps://gist.github.com/GNSPS/ba7b88565c947cfd781d44cf469c2ddb\r\n\r\nIt has been tested in production as you can see in the comments. Main improvements are the clear use of the `RETURNDATACOPY` opcode and usage of `DUP<X>` instead of pushing a lot of 0x00s.\r\n\r\n#### Cute Animal Picture\r\n\r\n![](https://secure.img2-ag.wfcdn.com/im/51042015/resize-h310-w310%5Ecompr-r85/4307/43074606/sitting-sleepy-bulldog-puppy-statue.jpg)\r\n\r\n",
